      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Barista Brewdown",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There have been three certainties this year: death, taxes, and Starbucks workers kicking company CEO Howard Schultz’s ass. The decrepit Schultz, whose own colossal self-regard forced him in 2022 out of a comfortable retirement, is now getting humiliated daily by 19-year-old baristas with piercings, BTS tattoos, and a strong desire to unionize. Over the past week, the Starbucks CEO was dealt union victories in stores in Connecticut, New York, Washington, Oregon, Kansas, Tennessee, Illinois, California, Michigan, Alabama, Louisiana, Minnesota, and Texas. In total, Starbucks workers have now voted to unionize in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "135",
